The paper focuses on state estimation for legged robots, specifically quadrupeds, which is a topic within robotics (cs.RO). The use of visual odometry and factor graph optimization suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The need for reliability in harsh conditions and the inclusion of inertial navigation suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). The use of optimization methods also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
